                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d621">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/505</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Person and property Irving L. Fisher at Victoria de Las Tunas are said to be in
                    imminent danger from insurrectionaries. Take matter up with Cuban State
                    Department, request that all possible steps be taken to insure safety of Fisher
                    and his property, and report regarding matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
